			<div class="content" id="post-content-2170234">
									

<ol>
<li>Unless I'm mistaken, the youngest Navy SEAL graduated BUDS at 15. Edit: I was mistaken. He was 17.</li>
<li>The narrator didn't become a SEAL until he was 19 and had been in the Navy for two years (granted, one of those years he was probably still in high school and was only in the Navy on paper, but still).</li>
<li>The story takes place nearly two decades after the narrator's Navy service, and exactly a decade after his MTF service.</li>
<li>The story is hardly about the narrator's badassery. I just have an unhealthy obsession with MTF Nu-7, and the person who made them specifically said they exclusively recruit from Navy and Marine Corps Spec Ops. I'm not gonna shit on their creation, regardless of death of the author.</li>
<li>The story, honestly, could have been from a researcher or more basic agent's perspective. The SEAL/Nu-7 thing was just personal choice.</li>
</ol>
<p>But as far as the &quot;too telly&quot; thing is concerned, you're right. This is very exposition-heavy. I wish I could change that, but then I'd be disqualified from the contest.</p>

