			<div class="content" id="post-content-2174512">
									

<p>Yeah, I know, all exposition and no plot makes Jack a dull boy. An earlier draft gave the two primary narrators more character, but my reviewers felt that the final section explaining their connection would work better, and it likely wouldn't have pulled it within your exposition tolerance limits, anyway. I haven't had much practice with &quot;show, not tell,&quot; and I was trying to create a cyberpunk/Orwellian dystopia with a mobile device and a short deadline, but my future contributions will be less exposition-heavy as a result of your's and other's feedback. I appreciate the input, thanks!</p>

